    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body>;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Az Egyesült Nemzetek Környezetvédelmi Programja"@hu, "Milieuprogramma van de Verenigde Naties"@nl, "United Nations Environment Programme"@en, "Programul Naţiunilor Unite pentru Mediu"@ro, "Clár Comhshaoil na Náisiún Aontaithe"@ga, "Förenta nationernas miljöprogram"@sv, "Programma delle Nazioni Unite per l’ambiente"@it, "Πρόγραμμα των Ηνωμένων Εθνών για το Περιβάλλον"@el, "Jungtinių Tautų aplinkos programa"@lt, "Program OSN pro životní prostředí"@cs, "Programme des Nations unies pour l’environnement"@fr, "Program OSN pre životné prostredie"@sk, "Umweltprogramm der Vereinten Nationen"@de, "ÜRO Keskkonnaprogramm"@et, "Il-Programm tan-Nazzjonijiet Uniti għall-Ambjent"@mt, "Apvienoto Nāciju Organizācijas Vides programma"@lv, "Yhdistyneiden kansakuntien ympäristöohjelma"@fi, "Програма на ООН за околната среда"@bg, "Programa de las Naciones Unidas para el Medio Ambiente"@es, "De Forenede Nationers miljøprogram"@da, "Program Narodów Zjednoczonych ds. Ochrony Środowiska"@pl, "Program Združenih narodov za okolje"@sl, "Program Ujedinjenih naroda za zaštitu okoliša"@hr, "Programa das Nações Unidas para o Ambiente"@pt;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Established pursuant to the recommendations of the United Nations Conference on the Environment. As of January 2015, it is composed of seven divisions: Division of Communications and Public Information, Division of Environmental Law and Conventions, Division of Environmental Policy Implementation, Division of Technology, Industry and Economics, Division of Early Warning and Assessment, Division of Global Environment Facility Coordination. Its mission is to provide leadership and encourage partnerships in caring for the environment by enabling nations and peoples to improve their quality of life without compromising that of future generations."@en;
