    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The L.69 Group of Developing Countries is a cross regional grouping of 42 developing countries from Africa, Latin America and the Caribbean, Asia and the Pacific, that is focused on achieving lasting and comprehensive reforms of the UN Security Council."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "COB0001081"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "L69"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "L69"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>;
