    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Mitmepoolsete Investeeringute Kaitse Keskus"@et, "Multilateral Investment Guarantee Agency"@en, "Mnohostranná agentúra pre investičné záruky"@sk, "Agence multilatérale de garantie des investissements"@fr, "Daugiašalių investicijų garantijų agentūra"@lt, "Organismo Multilateral de Garantía de Inversiones"@es, "Aġenzija Multilaterali għall-Garanzija ta’ Investiment"@mt, "Agência Multilateral de Garantia dos Investimentos"@pt, "Monenkeskinen investointitakuulaitos"@fi, "Daudzpusējo investīciju garantiju aģentūra"@lv, "Multilateraal Agentschap voor Investeringsgaranties"@nl, "Det Multilaterale Investeringsgarantiorgan"@da, "Multilaterális Beruházásbiztosítási Ügynökség"@hu, "Organisationen för multilaterala investeringsgarantier"@sv, "Agenția Multilaterală pentru Garantarea Investițiilor"@ro, "Agencija za multilateralna osiguranja investicija"@hr, "An Ghníomhaireacht Iltaobhach Rathú Infheistíochtaí"@ga, "Multilaterale Investitions-Garantie-Agentur"@de, "Agenzia multilaterale di garanzia degli investimenti"@it, "Multilateralna agencija za zavarovanje investicij"@sl, "Wielostronna Agencja Gwarancji Inwestycyjnych"@pl, "Multilaterální agentura pro záruky v investicích"@cs, "Многостранна (мултилатерална) инвестиционна агенция за гаранции"@bg, "Мултилатерална агенција за осигурање инвестиција"@sr, "Οργανισμός Πολυμερούς Ασφάλισης Επενδύσεων"@el;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "L’Agence multilatérale de garantie des investissements offre aux investisseurs des garanties contre les pertes associées aux risques non commerciaux dans les pays en développement."@fr, "On April 12, 1988 an international convention established MIGA as the newest member of the World Bank Group. The agency opened for business as a legally separate and financially independent entity. Membership was open to all IBRD members. MIGA was created to complement public and private sources of investment insurance against non-commercial risks in developing countries. MIGA’s multilateral character and joint sponsorship by developed and developing countries were seen as significantly enhancing confidence among cross-border investors. MIGA’s mission is to promote foreign direct investment into developing countries to support economic growth, reduce poverty and improve people’s lives."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "MIGA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "COB0001268"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "MIGA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>;
